jparsec.vo

Class Feed

  • java.lang.Object
    • jparsec.vo.Feed

  • public class Feed
extends java.lang.Object
    A class to read and write RSS feeds. Based on the tutorial at http://www.vogella.de/articles/RSSFeed/article.html Images are supported in messages using enclosures.
    Since:
    1.85
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    T. Alonso Albi - OAN (Spain)

      • Feed

        public Feed(java.lang.String title,
    java.lang.String link,
    java.lang.String description,
    java.lang.String language,
    java.lang.String copyright,
    java.lang.String pubDate,
    java.lang.String lastBuild,
    java.lang.String editor,
    java.lang.String webMaster,
    int ttl)
        Full constructor for a new feed (without an image).
        Parameters:
        title - The title.
        link - The main link to the site.
        description - The common description of the posts.
        language - The language abbreviation, en, es, and so on.
        copyright - Copyright message.
        pubDate - Publication date (beginning of the feed) string message. For instance, Fri, 29 Jul 2011 23:30:44 +0200.
        lastBuild - Date of the last build of the feed. Can be null.
        editor - Email of the editor. Can be null.
        webMaster - Email of the web master. Can be null.
        ttl - Number of minutes the feed can be cached before updating. Set to 0 to ignore this parameter.

      • createMessage

        public static FeedMessageElement createMessage(java.lang.String title,
                               java.lang.String description,
                               java.lang.String link,
                               java.lang.String author)
        Creates a simple feed message with no images.
        Parameters:
        title - The title.
        description - The description. It can contains links using the html a tag in a standard way, if it is rendered in html.
        link - The link associated to the message.
        author - The author.
        Returns:
        The feed message object.

      • createMessage

        public static FeedMessageElement createMessage(java.lang.String title,
                               java.lang.String description,
                               java.lang.String link,
                               java.lang.String author,
                               java.lang.String guid,
                               java.lang.String[] imgs,
                               java.lang.String pDate)
        Creates a simple feed message with images.
        Parameters:
        title - The title.
        description - The description.
        link - The link associated to the message.
        author - The author.
        guid - The Guid, to ensure the uniqueness of the message. It is identical (usually) to the link.
        imgs - The set of http urls to images inside the message.
        pDate - Publication date in a standard format, for instance Tue, 10 Jun 2003 04:00:00 GMT or Fri, 29 Jul 2011 23:30:44 +0200.
        Returns:
        The feed message object.
